        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"><small>USA</small></font>
        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"><small>50 Posts</small></font></td>
        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<a name="69898"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;09/11/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 12:51:23</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=6448"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=6448')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=AIM&amp;AIM=mneroneptg&amp;M_NAME=aazamn1')"><img src="icon_aim.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Send aazamn1 an instant message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=69898&amp;TOPIC_ID=8248&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Circlet+of+Shadow+Decision&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         CoS can't be in a container. But let's put it this way: I now carry one less pack so that my CoS is always in an inventory slot. I have it hotkeyed. Do it. It'll save your can. </P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>That request in mind, why the hell is the CoS so valuable? Pre-nerf is the near-insta invis, super low casting time? So...? I get that it saves you a spell slot, you never have to memorized Gather Shadows again... but still.</P><P>What makes it so great? In 31 levels I can honestly say I've never had a problem with Invis. Maybe I'm just too young, I sure hear classes that cant invis bitch about that fact enough.</P><P><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Here's an example for you. You realize that you're in trouble and you're going to have to run for zone. You're low on health and you know that if anything hits you you're dead. You also know that there are any number of creatures between you and the zone that will agro as you pass between/through/over them. With CoS you start running. You hit your hotkey and you're instant invis. You run straight through everything that would've killed you otherwise and make it to zone. </P><P>Here's another. You're trying to get to a group in whatever zone. You cast invis and start down. About the time you're in the worst possible area of the zone, you get the "you feel yourself starting to appear" mesg. Without a CoS it's panick time. You might get a gate off. You might get a feign off. But don't bet the bank on it when you're in a room overflowing with highly agro mobs. With CoS you instant cast invis again, and nothing ever sees you. You can stand on top of nastiest of mobs (that don't see invis) and spam cast CoS and they'll never know you're there. It instantly drops and recasts invis. </P><P>You feign death to get rid of agro. You know that particular mob is probably too high to forget you. If you stand and at the same time hotkey the CoS, he probably won't come after you as long as you wait until he's back at his spawn point.</P><P>You go LD in an area you cleared (outside or in). You know by the time you can log back in that respawn will have caught up to you. With CoS the instant you're in-game, you hit your CoS hotkey and invis up. No agro. </P><P>And finally, you really want to pull that named mob but you know you can't fight it anywhere near it's current location, and you know you can't handle all the mobs around him. Doens't matter if it's in a dungeon or outside. Doesn't matter if it's to solo or to pull for a group. With CoS you find a spot that you aren't going to take agro, nuke him once, hit your CoS hotkey, and run through any number of creatures to a spot where you know you can engage the mob safely. Most of the time, the one mob you want will run right over all the mobs meant to protect him and come straight to where you know you can smack him around. (This only works if you can single pull the mob already. But if usually works when the mobs normally would assist if the one you're pulling reaches them to "tell" them about you if you're already invis. They won't add.) This makes it possible to perform some amazing pulls and group's jaws hit the floor when you start single pulling names from all over the zone with no adds.</P><P>Priceless.</P><P>[edit] - And just to clarify in case you didn't know... CoS can be cast while you're running. You can be doing anything at all and invis at any time (as long as you're not already casting another spell and waiting for it to be interupted). </P><P></P><P></P><P>Edited by - aazamn1 on 09/11/2002  13:00:31<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

