        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Timdini, Everything in this thread is absolutely true. But the other thing worth mentioning is: the Circlet of Shadows will just plain enhance your enjoyment of the game. This is all about fun right? I would spend ANY amount of pp I had to make the game more enjoyable. The CoS will enable you to do things that you have probably not thought of before (why would you think of them...you couldn't do them without the CoS that you don't have), and it will keep you from dieing countless times which will also increase your enjoyment of the game. How many times have you paid a cleric for a res because the pp you spent was worth it to not have to re-earn xp? That's pp well spent for your enjoyment of the game and so is the CoS.</P><P>One other thing... the pre-nerf CoS is an artifact now. They don't drop and most likely never will again. Become part of an exclusive club that is diminishing as time goes by (and the CoS doesn't even exist on servers started after the CoS nerf). You really can't put a value on an item that cannot be obtained any more except through trading. I paid 15k for mine and drained my bank account totally... I can get more pp easily, but I'll NEVER loot a pre-nerf CoS off a mob. And even if you decided you don't like it (I can't imagine that), you can sell it and make some pp for yourself.</P><P>You have an opportunity to get an item that sets you apart from the crowd and increase your abilities in the game. There really is no big decision here... there is no downside to buying the CoS.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
